stix:Indicator.indicator:Title: Malicious File Indicator
stix:Indicator.indicator:Description: According to DHS and FBI analysis, "Inveigh-Relay.ps1" [MD5: 5DBEF7BDDAF50624E840CCBCE2816594] is used in conjunction with "Inveigh.ps1" [MD5: aa905a3508d9309a93ad5c0ec26ebc9b] to capture credentials and challenge/response hashes over the network. "Inveigh-Relay.ps1" also sets up its own interactive shell. By default "Inveigh-Relay.ps1" will proxy data over TCP Port 8182.
